			<h3 class="m-t-10"><i class="fa fa-cog"></i> Engaging Citizens across the City</h3>
			<hr>
			<p>
				Community engagement is what the City uses to get more people to participate in civic related activities, which includes voting, attending community events, volunteering, joining a City board or commission, getting to know neighbors and general community building. More civic participation strengthens democracy and increases the value of public institutions and infrastructure - meaning the more people participate, the stronger and more representative our city is.
			</p>
			<p>
				<h4>The Process</h4>
				The process of shaping community engagement policy can be initiated by anyone, but it must first pass through the proper official channels. The City’s Neighborhood and Community Relations department and resident-populated Neighborhood and Community Relations Commission report their ideas/concerns to the Health, Environment and Community Engagement (HECE) committee who is the lawmaking body who addresses community engagement-related issues.
			</p>
